    "body": "Problem: JSON files should end with a trailing newline so that Unix\r\n  tools work as expected, Git doesn't report \"No newline at end of file\"\r\n  and to avoid noise in diffs from editors and other tools adding the\r\n  missing newline.\r\n\r\nSolution: Add trailing newline.",
    "closed_at": "2026-03-24T17:23:18Z",
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I've encountered the side effects of this myself several times, but I am not an expert in this kind of things (file encoding, line endings, etc.). So just writing the `vim.json.encode()` output seems like a safer choice.\r\n\r\n@justinmk, but if you know that adding an explicit newline is okay and not breaking on some non-Unix tooling, then this looks fine to me.",
