        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Well, as a point of reference, `vim.fn.writefile(vim.split(vim.json.encode({a=1,b=2}, { indent = '  ' }), '\\n'), 'test-file.json')` *will* add a single `\\n` at the end (verified by `:=vim.fn.readblob('test-file.json')`). So it indeed looks like a good idea to add it here.",
