        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> I think it's easiest to just always add the newline if `indent` is specified.\r\n\r\nI don't think this should be changed. The current behavior matches `JSON.stringify` in JavaScript, `json.dumps` in Python, and `json.MarshalIndent` in Go (and all other popular JSON libraries, I believe).\r\n\r\n> @justinmayhew If I'm wrong, can you please link the source that says that a newline is necessary.\r\n\r\nYou're not wrong, but it's considered good hygiene for text files to have a trailing newline. `package-lock.json` files generated by `npm` have a trailing newline, so this follows the existing precedent.",
            "created_at": "2026-03-24T16:26:04Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38469#issuecomment-4119646463",
            "id": 4119646463,
            "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/issues/38469",
            "node_id": "IC_kwDOAPphoM71jND_",
            "performed_via_github_app": null,
            "reactions": {
                "+1": 1,
                "-1": 0,
