        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I agree that `vim.json.encode()` should not handle trailing newline. Appending it is the caller's responsibility when writing output to a file to follow POSIX conventions, whether the output is indented or not.",
            "created_at": "2026-03-24T17:19:08Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38469#issuecomment-4119990354",
            "id": 4119990354,
            "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/issues/38469",
            "node_id": "IC_kwDOAPphoM71khBS",
            "performed_via_github_app": null,
            "reactions": {
                "+1": 0,
                "-1": 0,
                "confused": 0,
                "eyes": 0,
                "heart": 0,
                "hooray": 0,
                "laugh": 0,
                "rocket": 0,
                "total_count": 0,
                "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/issues/comments/4119990354/reactions"
            },
            "updated_at": "2026-03-24T17:19:08Z",
            "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/issues/comments/4119990354",
            "user": {
                "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/101928759?v=4",
                "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/skewb1k/events{/privacy}",
                "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/skewb1k/followers",
                "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/skewb1k/following{/other_user}",
                "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/skewb1k/gists{/gist_id}",
                "gravatar_id": "",
                "html_url": "https://github.com/skewb1k",
                "id": 101928759,
                "login": "skewb1k",
                "node_id": "U_kgDOBhNPNw",
                "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/skewb1k/orgs",
                "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/skewb1k/received_events",
                "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/skewb1k/repos",
                "site_admin": false,
                "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/skewb1k/starred{/owner}{/repo}",
                "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/skewb1k/subscriptions",
                "type": "User",
                "url": "https://api.github.com/users/skewb1k",
                "user_view_type": "public"
            }
        },
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> > I think it's easiest to just always add the newline if `indent` is specified.\r\n> \r\n> I don't think this should be changed. The current behavior matches `JSON.stringify` in JavaScript, `json.dumps` in Python, and `json.MarshalIndent` in Go (and all other popular JSON libraries, I believe).\r\n\r\n:( Those have many different parameters, none of the various params support adding a final newline?\r\n\r\nEven if not, I still think we should consider it. It makes no sense at all to output \"human readable\" but then a trailing newline is considered improper.",
            "created_at": "2026-03-24T17:24:43Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38469#issuecomment-4120024549",
            "id": 4120024549,
            "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/issues/38469",
            "node_id": "IC_kwDOAPphoM71kpXl",
