        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> :( Those have many different parameters, none of the various params support adding a final newline?\r\n\r\nNot that I'm aware of.\r\n\r\n> Even if not, I still think we should consider it. It makes no sense at all to output \"human readable\" but then a trailing newline is considered improper.\r\n\r\nI agree it's a bit confusing. In many cases these JSON indent functions are used along with a `print()` that itself adds a newline, and it's nice that you don't get two trailing newlines in those scenarios.",
            "created_at": "2026-03-24T17:44:43Z",
